FBIS3-53466 "drnes011cc_94004" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 Islamic Affairs ICO Ministers Hold Two-Day Meeting on Bosnia UN Urged To Authorize NATO Strikes on Serbs LD1701154894 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1500 GMT 17 Jan 94 LD1701154894 Bern Swiss Radio International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Foreign ministers of the Islamic Conference Organization [ICO] have called on the United Nations secretary general, Butrus-Ghali, to authorize NATO air strikes against ethnic Serbians in Bosnia-Herzegovina. The secretary general of the ICO, Hamid al-Ghabid, made the call during a meeting between members of the Islamic organization and Mr. Butrus-Ghali in Geneva. The Islamic countries repeated a call for the European Union to end an arms embargo on Muslims in Bosnia to allow them to defend themselves against Serbian and Croatian attacks.
